description: Palindromes with exactly 9 palindromic prime factors (counted with multiplicity).
links: Lars Blomberg, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..234, terms < 10^16.
example: The palindrome 6338118336 is a term since it has 9 factors 2^6 3 11 3001003, all palindromic.
